<div id="review_139274390" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/139274390" />
    <a title="Amy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2329228-amy"><img alt="Amy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1433629372p2/2329228.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/139274390?book_show_action=true">Jan 08, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amy" href="/user/show/2329228-amy">Amy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781441753830" href="/book/show/10122473-the-road-to-serfdom">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=books-i-wouldn-t-mind-owning">books-i-wouldn-t-mind-owning</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=mind-blown">mind-blown</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=jurisprudence">jurisprudence</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=mr-baer-reccomended">mr-baer-reccomended</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2329228-amy?shelf=afp">afp</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer139274390" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10564671311930864876">There is something a little awe-inspiring about reading a book and realizing how much of your personal philosophy and intellectual heritage you owe to it. I got the same feeling the first time I read <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/137437.Two_Treatises_of_Government__Library_of_Primary_Sources_' title='Two Treatises of Government (Library of Primary Sources) by John Locke' rel='nofollow noopener'>Two Treatises of Government</a>. When I consider the impact this book has had on my life and work, it amazes me it took me this long to read it. <br/>This should be required reading alongside <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/40961427.1984' title='1984 by George Orwell' rel='nofollow noopener'>1984</a>. It conveys the problems of socialism and yet eerily resembles a conversation we could be having today. <br/>Thought-</span>
  <span id="freeText10564671311930864876" style="display:none">There is something a little awe-inspiring about reading a book and realizing how much of your personal philosophy and intellectual heritage you owe to it. I got the same feeling the first time I read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/137437.Two_Treatises_of_Government__Library_of_Primary_Sources_" title="Two Treatises of Government (Library of Primary Sources) by John Locke" rel="nofollow noopener">Two Treatises of Government</a>. When I consider the impact this book has had on my life and work, it amazes me it took me this long to read it. <br />This should be required reading alongside <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/40961427.1984" title="1984 by George Orwell" rel="nofollow noopener">1984</a>. It conveys the problems of socialism and yet eerily resembles a conversation we could be having today. <br />Thought-provoking and inspiring, I highly recommend this one. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10564671311930864876" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
